    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Aug 29<hi rend="superscript">th.</hi> 1777.</dateline>

                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>I can now thank you for the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0144">map of
                            Dundee</title></bibl> &amp;c which came safely from <persName ref="pe0026">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> White</persName>. Thanks also
                    for the future promised things.</p>
                <p>I hope <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> has
                    not been prolix. We english love conciseness.</p>
                <p>I have found <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0186">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Skinner’s traced map</title></bibl>. I see an inaccuracy,
                    for he has included the six northern parishes in <placeName ref="pl0825">Caithness</placeName>, which all speak english &amp; have no use of the
                    erse service. If you can, procure me the names of those parishes.</p>
                <p>The title to <persName ref="pe0139">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Lightfoots</persName> work is still <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0231">Flora scotica</title></bibl>.</p>
                <p>You cannot expect <persName ref="pe0026">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        White</persName> to send every purchaser of the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0010">Tours</title></bibl> a <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0209">map</title></bibl>: you see he has inscribed a
                    promisory note; <hi rend="underline">to the bearer of which he will deliver a
                        map.</hi><hi rend="superscript">x</hi><note type="authorial"><hi rend="superscript">x</hi> y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Booksellers
                        must send for them by means of the receit.</note> It is in the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0209">last volume</title></bibl>. So large an
                    impression was made of that, it is not yet sold.</p>


                <p>I will think about what is said of the <unclear reason="illegible">Cestus.</unclear></p>
                <closer><salute>I am Dear Sir <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> affect. humble
                            Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed></closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p>my respects &amp; thanks to <persName ref="pe0064">Lord Hailes</persName> for
                        his present.</p>
                    <p><persName ref="pe0246">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Pope</persName> long
                        since presented me with the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0087">translation of Torfæus</title></bibl>; but <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> had best use his
                        own.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom house</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Edinburgh</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
            </div>
